commit.message:
Only test a few versions on macOS.

Travis macOS tests are extremely slow, so we want to cut these out of
the loop to the extent possible.
Fix config for recent rubocop.
Use bundler 1.x in tests.

Fix integration tests: don't use EV DigiCert root.

www.mozilla.org has stopped using an EV certificate, so the root we need
to use has changed. Ideally we might pin to something that will
necessarily have a stable root certificate over time, such as
https://extended-validation.badssl.com.

Fix rubygems update for rubies < 2.3.

https://github.com/rubygems/rubygems/issues/2534
Drop ruby 2.0 from test matrix, update versions.
Update rubocop config for rubocop 0.54.

Merge pull request #630 from rest-client/ab-rubocop

Fix rubocop failures introduced by rubocop 0.50.
Fix rubocop failures introduced by rubocop 0.50.
Add http-accept to documented dependencies.

Update AUTHORS and import .mailmap.

I've been using this .mailmap file in order to update the AUTHORS with
`rake authors`.

Version 2.1.0.rc1

Freeze the version constants, and don't bother checking whether they're
already defined (that usually indicates a problem with requires).
Add history notes for 2.1.0 release candidate.

Merge pull request #615 from rest-client/ab-http-accept-content-type

Add dependency on http-accept for Content-Type.
Enable LineLength cop.
Fix deprecated names of rubocop cops.

Test with an image in the public domain. (#607)

Switch to using NASA photo S130-E-012142 of the ISS. It is in the public
domain because it is a work created solely by NASA.

Fixes: #606

Fix spurious rubocop warning around Exceptions.

These exceptions already inherited from RestClient::Exception, but
rubocop couldn't tell the difference between that and ::Exception.
